  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7 and boil a kettle, then take your <strong>chicken</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Chop your<strong> leek[s] </strong>into rounds and wash thoroughly to remove any grit, then slice your <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into thin discs</p><p>Add the <strong>sliced potato</strong> and <strong>leek</strong> <strong>rounds</strong> to a pot of plenty of<strong> boiled water</strong>, bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for 5-6 min or until softened slightly</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
