    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the veg has softened slightly, drain it and transfer to an <strong>oven-proof dish</strong> (save the pot!)</p><p>Meanwhile, melt 20g<span class=\"text-purple\"> [30g]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [40g]</span> <strong>butter </strong>in the reserved pot over a medium heat</p><p>Once melted, add 20g<span class=\"text-purple\"> [30g]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[40g]</span> <strong>flour</strong> and stir with a wooden spoon for 1 min or until a sandy paste forms – this is your <strong>roux</strong></p><p>Add 250ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[375ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[500ml]</span> <strong>milk </strong>gradually and whisk for 5 min or until a smooth, thick sauce remains – this is your <strong>béchamel sauce</strong></p>",
