    {
      "instruction": "<p>Dissolve your <strong>chicken stock mix</strong> in 175ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[230ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[300ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Once softened, add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> to the pot along with 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tsp]</span> <strong>flour </strong>and cook for 30 secs</p><p>Add the <strong>chicken stock</strong> to the pot and cook for 5-6 min or until reduced to a gravy-like consistency – this is your <strong>gravy</strong></p>",
