    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a knob of <strong>butter</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Wash, then rip the leaves off your <strong>spring greens</strong>, discard the tough stalks, then layer the leaves over each other, roll them up and slice into thin strips</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced spring greens</strong> and <strong>blanched peas</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until tender with a bite – these are your <strong>buttery greens</strong></p>",
